                    <div class="overview-description">
                        <p>
                            Fellowship Part 1 provides a comprehensive introduction to pediatric neuroradiology, 
                            covering essential imaging techniques, normal anatomy, common pathologies, and 
                            fundamental clinical skills. This program is designed for residents completing 
                            diagnostic radiology training or early-career radiologists seeking specialization 
                            in pediatric neuroradiology.
                        </p>
                        <p>
                            The curriculum combines theoretical knowledge with hands-on clinical experience, 
                            mentored by leading experts in the field. Fellows will develop competency in 
                            interpreting pediatric neuroimaging studies and gain exposure to interventional 
                            neuroradiology techniques.
                        </p>
                    </div>
